    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "2 PAN AMERICAN AIRWAYS SYSTEM.\n{ICAN",
      "AIRWAYS OBSERVERS, who were\naugural flight of F.A.M.-18, Northern Route, are shown entering the \"Yankee Clipper\"\nJune 24, 1939. Passenger at right (carrying coat and hat and waving) is Charles P.\nGraddick, Superintendent of Air Mail Service, Postoffice Department, Washington,\nwho was an observer on the initial flight. Graddick's numerous contributions to the\ndevelopment of a widespread and efficient service are well known in air mail circles."
    ],
